JAIROS SAUNYAMA POLICE in Marondera, Mashonaland East province, have launched investigations into a case where a woman was mysteriously burnt beyond recognition in her room in Dombotombo high-density suburb on Friday last
week. Provincial police spokesperson Inspector Simon Chazovachi confirmed the incident. “We can confirm that a woman, who could be in her early 40s, was burnt beyond recognition in Dombotombo high-density suburb and the cause of the fire is not yet known,” he said. According to police, the room caught fire at around 2am on Friday. l Follow Jairos on Twitter @jairossaunyama 